categories.name: Bread Delivery Services
categories.desc: Your personal bread concierge & catering service. Our dedicated drivers bring you everyday for one Month one Product from our Catalog of tasty bread.

categories.name: Unstable bread
categories.desc: We at Stable Bread believe that every generated bread should find a home. Here you will find our still mostly tasty products that did not make the cut for one reason or another.

products.name: The Crusty Ciabatta
products.desc: This fine loaf was made in the style of italian Ciabatta but somehow still got a nice crunchy crust. Pretty fluffy on the inside

products.name: The Multigrain Miracle
products.desc: If you're ever in need of a healthy snack or a perfect all-rounded base for your sandwich, the Multigrain Miracle has got you covered. Fresh and hefty, mmmm!

products.name: Langonian Loaf
products.desc: This elongated loaf is a tradition in the rural bakeries of Langonia, where the people are quiet but full of love for their culinary work. Enjoy a slice of culture.

products.name: Sourdough Surprise
products.desc: Wow! This delicious twist on the classic formula has a kick to it. Take a bite and your taste buds ignite.

products.name: Bodacious Baguette
products.desc: Who said that bread can't be fine dining? Treat yourself to a luxurious experience. Ooh la la...

products.name: Brioche Dream
products.desc: Soft as a pillow and light as a cloud, this sweet pastry will leave you lusting for more. Don't get lured too much by its charms!

products.name: The Classic
products.desc: Solid. Practical. Cheap. This classic creation is enjoyed by many factory workers of the world, sustaining and giving energy to society's backbone. Comes out a bit misshapen sometimes, because function over form.

products.name: Dangerous Liaison
products.desc: This product will look unassuming to most, but according to a local myth, the invention of this type of bread is attributed to the legendary Farmhand Josh, who once made a deal with the Devil to make his bread irresistible to the common folk. People came flocking, and eventually Josh was shot by a mysterious man in a cadillac. Rumors are that this was a henchman of Big Bread. Josh was too good for this world. Do you want to try the Devil's game?

products.name: Dwarven Deliciousness
products.desc: This loaf was engineered with precision by a Polish bakery guild that have a strange obsession with Dwarf culture. This bread's inventors claim that this recipe was handed to them by a Dwarf one fateful midnight. Questionable lore, but solid product.

products.name: Loaf of Nourishment
products.desc: Crafted with mathematical brilliance by the world's topmost food scientist to procure a loaf that maximizes fulfillment and nutrition over size and material cost, this is a little bundle of perfect biomechanical excellence for you to trust and enjoy.

products.name: Beloved Bun
products.desc: One of the most popular picks among our catalogue, this is the people's breakfast.

products.name: Stretchy Special
products.desc: Somehow, you can bend, squish, and stretch this bread into almost any geometrical shape you desire. Kids love it, parents fear it, food administrations don't know what to do.

products.name: Pane di Altamura
products.desc: Everything in this perfect little loaf is just right, from the flavourful and tasty insides to the thick, lovely crust. Molto bene!

products.name: Sirapslimpa
products.desc: Credited to a swedish househusband who got struck by a sudden genius, this heavenly creation goes best with some butter and cheese. Food for the soul.

products.name: Beekeper's Beauty
products.desc: Cherished by beekepers around the globe, just a bite of this will have you ready to get down and dirty with the earth's hardest workers. But watch out - every 1 in 100 or so of this bread can have a dead bee in it. Such is life for a beekeeper.

products.name: Lonely Bread
products.desc: Delicious on the inside, unassuming on the outside, generally left on the shelves by the mindless consumer and underappreciated in a competitive world. Don't you want to give this bread a home?

products.name: Sir John
products.desc: About as grey, rainy, mellow as the British countryside, but also distinguished and comes with a hint of legend and class within. Goes well with tea.

products.name: Frivolous Frenchie
products.desc: Buyer beware: Studies have shown that consuming too much of this one will increase flatulence by immediately noticeable and highly unwelcome amounts. Popular in France and honestly not really anywhere else.

products.name: Round Rye
products.desc: Attributed to Robyn R. Rydolin, this bundle of joy will get your day started right, or be a great companion for lunch or dinner, and even a sneaky midnight snack. Just an all-round must-have.

products.name: The Mistake
products.desc: Our intern made this up last week and we fired him. We don't know what he was thinking. Still edible despite terrible design.

products.name: All Apologies
products.desc: We're so sorry about this one. Try to cut around the mold. You have to understand, our policy is to not throw out any potential product. Any bread is welcome here. All in all is all we are.

products.name: Family Van
products.desc: This spacious, bulky vehicle has ample room for anything from marzipan pigs to gingebread man, safe and sound on wheels so round!

products.name: Stylish City Trotter
products.desc: Quick on the move, felixble and slim, this modern bread car is built for swift transport in slick style.

products.name: Stout Exotic Racer
products.desc: Powerful and speedy, this one has that little extra special sauce.

products.name: Exquisite Ride
products.desc: For distinguished drivers and grain transport connoisseurs, this is the dream. Built to last and just as artful as it is reliable.

products.name: Geometrically Impossible French Nightmare
products.desc: The brainchild of a french bicyclist with too much passion and a tendency to ask 'how'? before 'why?', this one comes at a discount price because driving comes with a non-negligable risk.

products.name: The Cookie Cab
products.desc: Crunchy and fabulous, this car is a sweet mobile treat.

products.name: Sugar Tank
products.desc: Watch out for this one! Nobody is safe from the Sugar Tank - packed with more deliciousness than you can handle, this all-out calorie war car might not crush opponents, but it will send them to the hospital.

products.name: Layered Larry
products.desc: A detailed and intricated design, this creation by high-end fashion visionary Larry Lavaire is sure to dazzle and wow any bystander with its eccentric charms.

products.name: Buddhist Bob
products.desc: How did he end up here? Sometimes our friend Bob here gets too high on yeast and thinks he's a car. Oh well. Try giving him a ride if you so choose. It should be a fun challenge.

products.name: Kiddie Nightmare
products.desc: Originally designed as an edible treat for children to teach them what a car is, the accidently horrifying face design has led it's target audience to cry and rip it apart most of the time.

products.name: Welsh Wonder
products.desc: Designed in the city of Llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogoch, this bread car comes with a long history despite its short stature. With cream cheese accents and sesame seeds in the base, this is a well refined cultural milestone.

products.name: Taxi With A Twist
products.desc: At first sight just your average trusty bread city transport, but on second look this bread taxi is equipped with a little extra roof baguette.

products.name: Filaxous Gnav
products.desc: This is a bread car for the real aficionados. You will not spot a more deftly constructed, functional yet beautiful bread car far and wide. Limited supply - be a proud owner of a Filaxous Gnav before it is too late.

products.name: Soda Street Driver
products.desc: What appears to be a porous spongy disaster to the uneducated eye is actually the height of current Irish soda bread technology. Applying creative baking techniques to the science of bread cars, this marriage of culinary and academic excellence will stand the test of time.

products.name: The Boss
products.desc: Simply put, an undeniable example of high-end bread cars for the affluent man. An affordable status symbol for the upper middle class.

products.name: English Cinnamon Ride
products.desc: A feast for eyes and taste buds alike, this layered and perfectly texutred treat is easily loveable and thoroughly pleasant.

products.name: Wacky Adventure Vessel
products.desc: The engineer that came up with this one might or might not have been off the hops putting this one on the drawing board. Fun guaranteed - safety not so much.

products.name: Wonky Oldie
products.desc: This nostalgic vehicle has been through a lot. Take proper care of it!

products.name: Bullet Bus
products.desc: Aeordynamic and built for mass transport. Even loaded with hoardes of dough based inhabitants, this bread bus will speed through any area like clockwork. No time wasted, and no excesses in design.

products.name: The Most Stable Of Them All
products.desc: Unable to actually move due to a lack of wheels, this bread car does not go anywhere (...except into your mouth! yim yum)

products.name: Porous Traveller
products.desc: Balanced precariously on delicious rings, this featherweight car is not very practical, but it is a fanficul sight for anyone.

products.name: Jesse Breadmen
products.desc: He is channeling his inner 1920 delivery boy with that cart.

products.name: Mustafa Leipämann
products.desc: How can you not trust him with that smile.

products.name: Cereal Breadder
products.desc: Better watch out if you are allergic to gluten.

products.name: Brother's Bread Van
products.desc: These two brothers do not fear any distance when it comes to delivering bread.

products.name: Edward Breadward
products.desc: You better be on team edward.

products.name: Leonardo Breadbox
products.desc: He has been completely consumed by his desire for bread.

products.name: Vin Cheesebread
products.desc: He is coming to to town and delivers your cheesy bread.

products.name: Anon Bread
products.desc: He does not want to be seen but does deliver on time! May talk about some strange image boards though...

products.name: Arnold Schwarzbreadder
products.desc: He works out just to carry all that bread.

products.name: Tom
products.desc: Just Tom doing some deliveries.

products.name: Pumpkin bread
products.desc: We thought it looked like an overripe pumpkin, so we decided to make it the same size.

products.name: Heavy bread
products.desc: This bread is so dense with nutriens that its weight bent the wheel rims on our van.

products.name: Pillow bread
products.desc: Noah went to Ikea and thought he bought lots of bread for his shop, but he forgot to check that is was real bread.

products.name: Pine bread
products.desc: There isn't anything pine-related in this bread, it just looks like a pine cone.

products.name: Airbag bread
products.desc: Due to the high rate of injuries when bikes are in an accident we developed the Airbag bread. It cushions the impact and is a convinient source of carbs for long bike rides.

products.name: Reststop bread
products.desc: Jackson had enough of stale Sandwiches at Highway reststops. So he decided to start his own company and sell fresh bread from his van at reststops.

products.name: Shadow bread
products.desc: This is not real bread, DO NOT TRUST IT! It is a ploy by the shadow people.

products.name: Delivery bread
products.desc: Do desire fresh bread,b ut your depressions doesn't let you get up from the couch? Well now you can get your bread delivered.

products.name: Vietnamese bread
products.desc: If you have ever been on the streets of Bangkok you know what I am referring to.

products.name: British bread
products.desc: If you look closely you can almost see that there is no flavor in this bread at all.

products.name: Golf bread
products.desc: If you eat this bread, it will help you improve your swing.

products.name: Chanel bread
products.desc: Chanel decided to make designer bread, it looks good but is simply impractical.

products.name: Unit bread
products.desc: Metric units were too difficult for Chad and he got the unit conversions totally wrong when baking. But it is also an absolute unit.

products.name: Eastern european bread
products.desc: By all accounts the bread made by your babushka will always be the best bread you ever had.

products.name: North-Korean Propaganda bread
products.desc: Bread for the people of the DPRK.

products.name: Russian bread
products.desc: Bread isn't that complicated but it still somehow smells faintly of vodka.

products.name: Traditional bread
products.desc: This bread was made like it was centuries ago.

products.name: Ultimate hotdog buns
products.desc: Now you just need some sausages of similar size.

products.name: Euphoric bread
products.desc: Bread that makes everyone happy.

products.name: Winter bread
products.desc: With current world events it may be a good idea to stock up on some bread.

products.name: Baby bread
products.desc: No this isn't bread for babies, but Sandra feels like a mother when holding this loaf.

products.name: Student bread
products.desc: Did a university of you ever have a normal hobby? Well, we all know the answer, but at least Kim here only bakes way too much bread.

products.name: Childrens book bread
products.desc: Did you expect a childrens book to keep a consistent style?

products.name: Baking course bread
products.desc: Karen is very happy with the result from here first baking course.

products.name: Carpenters bread
products.desc: Carpenters are always hungry because of all the physical labor. So Chantal decided to suprise her colleagues with some bread.

products.name: Workplace bread
products.desc: Olivia felt that her life was empty at her 9-to-5 job, so she decided to tale up baking as a hobby. Here colleagues are not complaining.

products.name: French bread
products.desc: The french are at it again, trying to best the germans at making bread, but it isn't working out for them.

products.name: Bread brick
products.desc: In an innovative practice to make the construction industry more climate friendly, houses can now be constructed from bread bricks.

products.name: Mardi Gras bread
products.desc: This Mardi Gras you can dress up as bread.

products.name: American propaganda bread
products.desc: Lets just ban sliced bread for some reason (American Politicians January 18, 1943).

products.name: Car bread
products.desc: Samantha doubled down on her bakery plans by buying a car that looks like bread for marketing purposes.

products.name: Fashian bread
products.desc: Last time we had a fashion show in a literal mud pit, this time fresh bread is the hot stuff in the New York fashion week.

products.name: Disappointment cookies
products.desc: These cookies illicit the same feelings, as the ice cream that is supposed to look like Spongebob.

products.name: Mind-controlled ghost cookies
products.desc: They should have worn aluminium foil on their head instead.

products.name: Play-Doh cookies
products.desc: These will trick you into thinking they aren't edible because they look like Play-Doh.

products.name: Pumpkin-Penguin cookie
products.desc: A cookie depicting a penguin in pumpkin.

products.name: Pumpkin ghost cookies
products.desc: Why not combine the best of halloween.

products.name: Pumkin cookies
products.desc: Cookies that look and taste like pumpkin.

products.name: Skull chocolate cookie
products.desc: These skeletons like chocolate a little bit too much and got it all over their jaws.

products.name: Hallowen Grinch cookies
products.desc: The grinch came a bit early this year and is now trying to fit in.

products.name: Childrens Halloween cookies
products.desc: These were made by children and you can see it.

products.name: Dark chocolate halloween cookies
products.desc: These are as bitter as my ex-wife.

products.name: Bowling on halloween cookies
products.desc: For some reason someone decided to make bowling balls out of pumkins.

products.name: Eyebrow cookies
products.desc: Even on halloween eyebrows are important

products.name: Cartoon cookies
products.desc: These cookies are what happens when you bake with an artist from a childrens cartoon.

products.name: Void cookies
products.desc: Dont worry it calls for you so nicely.

products.name: The basic cookies
products.desc: These are all you need to halloween.

products.name: Minimalist cookies
products.desc: Cookies made by halloween minimalists, a bit weird, but who are we to judge.

products.name: Radioactive cookies
products.desc: The green stuff on their head is obviously radioactive, I have seen more than enough cartoons.

products.name: Blues clues cookies
products.desc: The characters don't look quite like we remembered.

products.name: Creepy Buddies
products.desc: Though they might look cute, these round spooksters have a devilish kick to them.

products.name: Perilous Pumpkins
products.desc: These grimacing pumpkin sweets make a fine addition to any spooky event.

products.name: Skeleton Treat
products.desc: Sweeten your halloween party with this spooky skeletal surprise!

products.name: Almond bread
products.desc: Rather than bread containing almond this is bread made to look like chopped almonds.

products.name: Military bread
products.desc: SPECIAL OFFER: Bread has been used for experimental ballistics testing, it only has a few more holes otherwise it is as good as new.

products.name: Kudde bröd
products.desc: The lastest trend is stylize your entire bed and with kudde bröd you can make your bed look like bread.

products.name: Treasure bread
products.desc: If you look closely you can spot a map on this heap of bread, it might lead you to treasure!

products.name: Cartel bread
products.desc: No officer I am just a bread merchant the white substance stuffed inside is just flour. You know the kind you make bread from.

products.name: Hulk bread
products.desc: Just like the Hulk it has been heavily irradiated, but it only acquired a slight green tint. Otherwise it is just ordinary bread.

products.name: Fish bread
products.desc: It is bread that looks like fish and not bread that has fish on top.

products.name: Seafood bread
products.desc: We added some crab shells to the bread in order to make it more appealing. Additionaly it comes with the obligatory food poisioning as expected from seafood.

products.name: Bread castle
products.desc: If you build your walls from bread they can't starve you during a siege.

products.name: Bread basket
products.desc: It is just a small basket of soggy bread in an old and rundown diner.

products.name: Vegan brunch
products.desc: Do you want to have a brunch with your friends but that one person always complains that there are no vegan options, then this product is for you.

products.name: Mushroom bread
products.desc: In the grim darkness of the future a fungus exterminate all known species of grain. Humanity decided to fight fire with fire and grow bread from mushrooms.

products.name: Illuminati bread
products.desc: Don't ask and we won't have any problems.

products.name: Hipster bread
products.desc: It is just normal bread but some hipster with a beard and in a flanel shirt won't accept it.

products.name: Ancient bread
products.desc: The art of bread making has existed for thousands of years and these are some of the oldest examples of bread ever discovered as they are already partially fossilized.

products.name: Picasso bread
products.desc: Do you want people to think that you are a true connoisseur of art but simply can't afford a real painting from Picasso? Then Picasso bread is your number one choice for interior design. (Just don't let it near your ears.)

products.name: The bread of Silence
products.desc: Do you own a parakeet? Is it always too loud no matter what you do? Then the bread of silence is for you! Simply put it in the cage and after a few minimutes the animated mass of bread will have silenced your bird... permanently.

products.name: Möbius bread
products.desc: Have you ever felt the need for existential dread and a desire for fresh bread, then möbious bread is all you need. You can see it twist in multiple dimensions while also twisting your taste bust to unforseen flavors.

products.name: Knitted bread sweater
products.desc: The knitted bread sweater combines the best of two worlds. It keeps you warm like freshly baked bread and acts as a convenient snack. Also removes the need for deodarant as you will always smell of fresh bread.

products.name: Dumpster bread
products.desc: I have found this here bread in a dumpster behind a bakery. It might still be usefull to someone. I just need money to fuel my bread addiction.

products.name: Universual bread-based grease
products.desc: Leads to unintended side effects if it comes in contact with skin.
